About

La Cruche was formed in 2020 between 10 friends eager to make the most of our shared passion for golf. The French name, La Cruche, translates to 'The Jug', paying homage to the La Cruche trophy pictured below. Found in an unused cupboard by Harry FitzGerald, it became the perfect addition to the tour (apparently some other golf tournament have a similar trophy).

It would be remiss to say that La Cruche isn't competitive, but it certainly isn't all about taking our beloved trophy home. With handicaps ranging from 9 to 20 amongst the members, the golf isn't of the highest quality

During a relaxation in COVID restrictions, the founding 8 members of La Cruche seized the opportunity to embark on our first Tour, Northern Ireland. Read all about the Northern Ireland Tour here.

) } export default About
